&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;TRUST DOCTOR (F3) – Acute Medicine&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applications are invited for up to a year post of F3 Level Trust Doctor in Acute Medicine. An exciting opportunity has arisen in Acute Medicine at Dorset County Hospital NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post is based in our Acute Medicine Service, primarily on our Medical Assessment Unit (Ilchester Unit). We are looking for an enthusiastic doctor who is either looking to develop their Acute Medicine experience before applying for specialist training or looking for a trust grade post to continue their own personal development in this area. The post will not routinely include on call commitments.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post would be well suited to a doctor interested in gaining experience and training in a friendly, energetic and ambitious hospital set in beautiful part of the South coast of England. The post is available immediately, for a period of six months.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post is based in Dorset County Hospital which is one of the top performing hospitals in England, with an excellent reputation for delivering high quality care. It is set in the market town of Dorchester in the picturesque county of Dorset on the southern coast of England.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants are welcome to visit the hospital and meet the staff in the department either during the morning of the interview date or at other convenient times by arrangement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameFrances SwatridgeJob titleJunior Doctor Rota Co-ordinatorEmail addressfrances.swatridge@dchft.nhs.ukTelephone number01305 253199&lt;/p&gt;
